        "content": "<p>so we have <a href=\"https://www.roc-lang.org/builtins/List#range\"><code>List.range</code></a> but sometimes all I want to do is to <code>walk</code> over a range. It would be both more concise and also better for performance to have a <code>Num.walkRange</code> which did this without creating an intermediate list:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">walkRange</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">start</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">At</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">After</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">)],</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">end</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">At</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Before</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Length</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Nat</span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">step</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">?</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Num</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">state</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>thoughts?</p>",
        "id": 407094634,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1702232780
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it would read nicer to have it split up into <code>range</code> and <code>walk</code>. It seems like a compiler optimization could improve the performance easily.</p>",
        "id": 407095620,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1702233791
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are we planning on having something like iterators/generators? That could solve the performance issue</p>",
        "id": 407096035,
        "sender_full_name": "LoipesMas",
        "timestamp": 1702234219
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the plan is not to have something like those</p>",
        "id": 407096054,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1702234260
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and yeah it's true that optimizations in the future should make the perf equivalent</p>",
        "id": 407096079,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1702234296
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think we should only add that if it is for perf reasons.</p>",
        "id": 407096243,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1702234445
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Otherwise just <code>List.range |&gt; List.walk</code></p>",
        "id": 407096250,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1702234459
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <code>Num.walk</code> is pretty clear name? There's not really any other meaningful basic walk you can do over numbers.</p>\n<p>I would expect that a walk over a range is a pretty-straightforward pattern to optimize in theory, but walking over a range is a common enough need to be worth its own function.</p>",
        "id": 407097387,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1702235414
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I imagine that <code>Num.walk n</code> would walk from 0 to n rather than taking an arbitrary range</p>",
